1. *Radnici* su se pobunili protiv povećanja radnog vremena. (Workers* revolted against the increase in working hours.)
2. Sve više *radnika* odlazi u inostranstvo u potrazi za boljim poslom. (More and more *workers* are leaving abroad in search of better job opportunities.)
3. *Radnicima* će biti isplaćena naknada za prekovremeni rad. (*Workers* will be paid compensation for overtime work.)
4. Firma je zaposlila nove *radnike* kako bi povećala proizvodnju. (The company hired new *workers* to increase production.)
5. *Radnici* su odlučili da organizuju štrajk zbog loših radnih uslova. (*Workers* have decided to organize a strike due to poor working conditions.)
6. Ova firma nudi odlične uslove za *radnika* koji su spremni da se posvete poslu. (This company offers excellent conditions for *workers* who are willing to dedicate themselves to work.)
7. Za *radnike* je važno da imaju dovoljno slobodnih dana kako bi se odmorili. (*Workers* need to have enough days off to rest.)
8. Direktor je pohvalio *radnike* za njihov trud i zalaganje na poslu. (The director praised the *workers* for their effort and dedication at work.)
9. *Radnici* su bili veoma zadovoljni kada su dobili povećanje plate. (*Workers* were very satisfied when they received a pay raise.)
10. U ovoj fabrici ima mnogo stranih *radnika* koji su došli da rade u Srbiji. (There are many foreign *workers* in this factory who have come to work in Serbia.)